description: Amid rising tensions with Pakistan, the home ministry has directed all states and UTs to conduct civil defence drills across 244 districts on Wednesday. This large-scale exercise aims to enhance preparedness against potential attacks, simulating wartime scenarios to test evacuation plans, communication systems, and the functionality of civil defence services. The drills will involve civilians, students, and volunteers, focusing on training and assessing operational coordination.
title: First since 1971: MHA orders nationwide security drills to prepare for any attack

description: Russian President Vladimir Putin, in a call with PM Modi, strongly condemned the Pahalgam terrorist attack, emphasizing the need to bring perpetrators and supporters to justice. This endorsement of India's stance comes amid international calls for de-escalation. Putin accepted Modi's invitation to visit India for the annual summit, reaffirming the strength and resilience of the India-Russia strategic partnership.
title: In call to PM Modi, Putin backs India, says no compromise on terror

description: India's naval power is set to increase with the imminent commissioning of INS Tamala, a stealth frigate from Russia, following its sister ship INS Tushil. The Navy and DRDO successfully tested indigenous underwater mines, enhancing undersea warfare capabilities. These advanced Krivak-III class frigates, equipped with Brahmos missiles and other weapons, will bolster India's blue water operations.
title: India to soon get 2nd advanced stealth frigate built in Russia

description: Cyber-attacks originating from Pakistan have escalated, targeting Indian defense entities. The website of Armoured Vehicles Nigam Limited (AVNL) was defaced, and hackers claim to have accessed sensitive data from the Military Engineering Services (MES) and MP-IDSA. Authorities are taking measures to bolster security, audit systems, and enhance digital defenses against further intrusions.
title: Pakistani hackers claim to have breached many Indian defence sites

description: The Supreme Court modified a Bombay High Court order, directing Maharashtra's DGP to supervise the SIT probing allegations against policemen in the Badlapur 'fake' encounter case. This case involves the custodial death of Akshay Shinde, accused of sexual assault. The SIT will be constituted by the DGP, who will select appropriate officers for the investigation, with the state CID required to hand over relevant documents within two days.
title: SC allows DGP to oversee SIT in Badlapur death case

description: The Supreme Court declined a PIL seeking action against BJP MP Nishikant Dubey for allegedly criticizing the CJI and SC. The bench stated it would issue a short order explaining the dismissal. Another PIL concerning tourist safety in J&K after the Pahalgam attack was also dismissed, with the court criticizing the petitioner's motives and accusing him of seeking publicity.
title: SC refuses to entertain PIL against BJP MP Nishikant Dubey's outburst

description: The Supreme Court has taken a stern view of the misuse of free speech to mock individuals with physical disabilities. The court summoned comedian Samay Raina and four other influencers following a PIL accusing them of denigrating the dignity of the physically challenged on online platforms.
title: SC summons comedian Raina & 4 others over demeaning PWDs

description: The Supreme Court condemned caste-based discrimination within the judiciary, highlighting the targeting of a judicial officer in Punjab due to his lower caste origin as a cobbler's son. The court upheld the Punjab and Haryana High Court's decision to reinstate Prem Kumar, an additional district and sessions judge, who was unfairly dismissed.
title: Targeted because of cobbler's son, SC reinstates Punjab judicial officer

description: The Supreme Court intervened in the case of Kabir Paharia, who was previously deemed ineligible for MBBS due to his disability. After multiple rejections, the court ordered AIIMS, New Delhi, to grant him admission in the 2025-26 session, citing a violation of his fundamental rights. The court also directed the National Medical Commission to revise disability assessment guidelines, emphasizing functional ability over the extent of disability.
title: Thrice rejected for MBBS, disabled to get entry to AIIMS

description: Defence Minister Rajnath Singh conveyed to his Japanese counterpart General Nakatani India's concerns regarding Pakistan's continued support for cross-border terrorism and its role in nuclear proliferation, which threatens regional stability. Both nations condemned terrorism and pledged to enhance global cooperation to counter cross-border threats, with Japan expressing solidarity with India following the Pahalgam attack.
title: Amid Pak's reckless missile tests, Japan backs India's war on terror

description: West Bengal CM Mamata Banerjee has blamed BSF for instigating the Murshidabad violence, alleging their firing on protesters led to subsequent deaths. She criticized the BJP for focusing on Murshidabad while ignoring Manipur and other troubled states. Banerjee accused the BJP of hiding the riot victims' families to prevent her from providing compensation and using them to criticize her.
title: BSF incited flare-up in Murshidabad: West Bengal CM Mamata Banerjee

description: A judicial panel submitted a report to CJI Sanjiv Khanna regarding the alleged cash discovery at Justice Yashwant Varma's residence following a fire. The inquiry, triggered by the mysterious disappearance of cash captured in a video, involved examining over 50 witnesses, including top Delhi officials.
title: Cash at judge's house: Panel submits report

description: In a significant setback for the Madhya Pradesh STF, a CBI court in Bhopal acquitted Sajan Singh Thakur, a police constable, in the Vyapam scam. Thakur was accused of using a proxy in the 2013 recruitment test, but the court cited inconclusive forensic results and lack of evidence. This marks the first acquittal of a candidate in the massive exam fraud case, raising questions about the prosecution's case.
title: Cop becomes 1st ‘candidate’ acquitted in Vyapam case

description: A sessions court in Mumbai upheld a magistrate's decision to grant temporary custody of a 16-year-old son to his mother, dismissing the father's appeal. The court emphasized that a parent's mental illness doesn't automatically disqualify them from custody unless the child's welfare is endangered. The judge prioritized the child's welfare and noted the magistrate's thorough consideration of the case, including interaction with the child and mediation efforts.
title: Court: Mental illness no bar to custody unless danger to kid

description: The CUET-UG 2025, now starting May 13, faces delays and communication gaps, causing anxiety among 13.5 lakh applicants. The NTA will conduct the exam entirely in CBT mode for all 37 subjects. City slips, containing exam dates, are expected soon, as candidates prepare for a condensed schedule, with English and the General Test being the most popular subjects.
title: CUET-UG 2025 put off, exams to begin from May 13 instead of May 8

description: Uttarakhand experienced an alarming surge in rainfall, exceeding normal levels by 490% in the last 24 hours, with some areas surpassing 1,000%. The excessive rain caused Kempty Falls to swell, triggering landslides that blocked highways and damaged property. Authorities have issued red and orange alerts for several districts, prompting disaster management to prepare for potential emergencies and halt pilgrimages.
title: Landslide strikes Kempty Falls amid U’khand deluge

description: A dispute has erupted between Odisha and Bengal over the naming of a newly inaugurated Jagannath temple in Digha as "Jagannath Dham," with Odisha threatening legal action. Bengal's Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee retaliated, accusing Odisha of jealousy and targeting Bengalis. The conflict has ignited social media campaigns and accusations of discrimination against Bengali-speaking people in BJP-governed states.
title: Now, Odisha threatens to sue over ‘dham’ in Digha

description: The Supreme Court has expressed serious concerns about high court judges delaying judgments indefinitely, violating the right to speedy justice. It directed all High Courts to provide details of cases with reserved judgments pending pronouncement before January 31. Following this directive, Jharkhand HC promptly delivered verdicts in long-pending appeals, acquitting convicts, and scheduled orders for other delayed cases.
title: ‘Orders reserved for eternity’: SC asks HCs for pending cases data

description: Amidst a water release dispute with Haryana, the Punjab government justified its deployment of a large police force at the Nangal Dam by citing heightened India-Pakistan tensions following the Pahalgam terror incident. This explanation was presented to the Punjab and Haryana High Court, which is hearing petitions from the Bhakra Beas Management Board (BBMB) and others regarding Punjab's actions.
title: Punjab govt says Nangal Dam police deployment linked to India-Pak tension

description: The Russian Embassy in New Delhi will honour former Odisha CM Biju Patnaik on Victory Day, commemorating the Soviet Union's victory over Nazi Germany. Russian Ambassador Denis Alipov invited Naveen Patnaik to the event, where External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar will be the chief guest. Biju Patnaik is recognized for his participation in the Stalingrad Operation and support to the Red Army during World War II.
title: Russia to fete former Odisha CM Biju Patnaik for role in Stalingrad op

description: The Supreme Court has raised concerns about the Enforcement Directorate (ED) making unsubstantiated allegations in money laundering cases, highlighting a pattern of lacking evidence to link accused individuals to proceeds of crime. This observation arose during a bail hearing for an accused in the Chhattisgarh liquor scam, where the court questioned the ED's evidence linking the accused to a specific amount of illicit funds.
title: SC: Trend of ED making allegations against accused without evidence

description: The Allahabad High Court's Lucknow bench dismissed a PIL questioning Rahul Gandhi's citizenship, advising the petitioner to pursue other legal options. The court cited the Union government's inability to provide a timeline for resolving the complaint. A BJP worker alleged Rahul held British citizenship, making him ineligible to be an MP, but the Centre awaits information from the UK government.
title: Allahabad HC disposes of petition challenging Rahul Gandhi’s citizenship

description: India has expressed strong concerns to Canada regarding a parade in Toronto featuring anti-India imagery and threatening language. The Indian government urges Canadian authorities to take action against anti-India elements promoting hatred, extremism, and separatism. This issue continues to strain bilateral relations despite India's willingness to collaborate with the new Canadian government.
title: India conveys its concern to Canada over anti-Hindu rally

description: CJI Sanjiv Khanna has passed the decision on the validity of the Waqf Amendment Act, 2025 to incoming CJI B R Gavai, scheduling a hearing for May 15. The decision came after the court reviewed the Centre's response, noting the need for detailed examination of waqf property registration and related figures. The government maintains the Act benefits the Muslim community, while petitioners have raised concerns.
title: No stay, next CJI B R Gavai to decide waqf Act validity

description: Rajasthan government's plan to rename Mount Abu as 'Abu Raj Tirth' faces strong opposition from 23 local organizations, fearing a shift from a tourist destination to a religious site. Stakeholders worry that the proposed name change, coupled with potential restrictions on meat and alcohol, could collapse tourism and lead to mass unemployment. Concerns are rising about the hill station's identity and its attractiveness to visitors.
title: Rajasthan govt plan to rename Mt Abu, ban booze and non-veg, sparks protests

description: CBI Director Praveen Sood is likely to receive a one-year extension, amidst indications of disagreement within the selection committee, comprising PM Modi, CJI Khanna, and LoP Gandhi. Sources suggest the Congress leader hasn't approved any potential successors. Sood's initial two-year term concludes next month. Several senior IPS officers, including Sanjay Arora, Manoj Yadav, and Kailash Makwana, are being considered.
title: Selection panel 'differs', CBI chief may get 1-year extension

description: Following a tragic hospital balcony collapse in Jamshedpur that claimed three lives, individuals are emerging to claim government compensation, despite the deceased being abandoned during their lives. Hospital staff report that David Johnson, Lukas Tirki, and Srichand Tati had no visitors, but now relatives are appearing, seeking the bodies and the ex gratia payment.
title: After govt announces Rs 5L ex gratia, dead Jamshedpur patients get sudden kin

description: Great news for air travelers as Delhi Airport's main runway 10/28 is set to reopen this Tuesday. The Directorate General of Civil Aviation has approved the reopening after inspecting the upgraded runway. This move aims to alleviate the massive flight delays and diversions experienced recently. However, the runway will be closed again from mid-June to mid-September 2025 for further work.
title: Delhi airport’s closed runway to open today

description: Elon Musk is embroiled in disputes with his Texas neighbors over his compound plans. Complaints include zoning violations, excessive security measures like high fences and cameras, and alleged harassment. A homeowners association head, Paul Hemmer, has been particularly vocal, claiming constant surveillance and indecent behavior accusations.
title: Elon Musk seems to have neighbourhood problem in Texas, where he ...

description: Following the suspension of the Indus Water Treaty, India has initiated flushing and desilting of reservoirs on the Chenab River to improve water storage for the winter months. This action is part of a broader strategy to regulate the flow of western rivers into Pakistan. India also plans to expedite hydropower projects and explore additional measures to maximize water utilization.
title: Flushing & desilting used as tools to cut water flow to Pakistan

description: In a shocking incident near Nishat, Srinagar, a nomadic woman was allegedly raped and murdered, triggering widespread outrage. Police have arrested four men suspected of the heinous crime, which occurred while the victim was grazing her goats. Political figures are condemning the act, highlighting concerns about substance abuse and demanding justice for the victim and her family.
title: Four held for nomadic woman’s ‘rape-murder’ in J&K

description: Following a series of student suicides, IIT-Kharagpur is considering easing academic pressures. The institute plans to reform its attendance policy to better balance student well-being and academic demands. This decision comes after the recent deaths of multiple students, prompting a review of policies that may contribute to student stress.
title: IIT-Kharagpur relaxes rules after suicides

description: Following a terror attack and the suspension of the Indus Water Treaty, India has restricted water flow from the Baglihar and Salal dams on the Chenab River. This unprecedented action led to dramatically low water levels, allowing residents to walk across the riverbed for the first time in memory. The move highlights India's ability to regulate water resources and has sparked debate over the treaty's impact on the region.
title: India makes Chenab run dry, for now

description: Mehbooba Mufti has strongly criticized the government's decision to close tourist destinations in Kashmir following the Pahalgam attack, highlighting the negative impact on tourism and local livelihoods. She voiced concern over the widespread detention of locals, including vendors and ponywallahs, and cautioned against collective punishment and the alienation of the Kashmiri people. Mufti urged financial assistance for tourism-dependent workers ahead of the Amarnath Yatra.
title: Pahalgam attack: Mehbooba slams closure of tourist spots, detention of locals

description: Chief Minister Omar Abdullah emphasized that the Pahalgam terror attack would not impede governance and development in Jammu and Kashmir, echoing the central government's sentiment. He resumed office in Srinagar, prioritizing action, accountability, and inclusive development. Abdullah highlighted the importance of a smooth Amarnath Yatra and the anticipated inauguration of the Kashmir rail link to boost the region.
title: Pahalgam attack should not derail governance and development in J&K: Omar

description: Pakistan's military recently conducted successful test launches of its Fatah and Abdali missiles, showcasing enhanced precision and range amid regional tensions. These tests, part of Exercise INDUS, aim to validate technical parameters and ensure operational readiness. The actions underscore Pakistan's commitment to bolstering its defense capabilities in response to perceived threats and escalating tensions with India.
title: Pakistan test-fires missile amid escalating tensions with India

description: Security forces in Jammu and Kashmir's Poonch district have successfully dismantled a terrorist hideout in the Surankote area, recovering a cache of IEDs concealed in tiffin boxes and steel buckets. The operation, conducted by a joint team, also led to the seizure of wireless communication equipment and other materials. This discovery has thwarted potential terrorist attacks in the region, prompting ongoing search operations.
title: Poonch terror hideout busted, tiffin-box IEDs seized

description: UIDAI successfully tested Aadhaar-based face authentication for NEET UG 2025 in New Delhi, in collaboration with NIC and NTA. This pilot project marks the first use of facial biometrics in a major Indian entrance exam, aiming to enhance security and verify identities contactlessly.
title: In major exam-security boost, UIDAI tests face ID at NEET-UG

description: Rajasthan ACB recovered ₹20 lakh bribe money from Indira Gandhi Nagar, a day after BAP MLA Jaikrishn Patel's personal assistant fled with it during an entrapment operation. The cash, allegedly from a mine operator, was buried under a lawn. Patel, arrested on Sunday, is now in ACB custody for two days.
title: ACB digs up Rajasthan MLA's Rs20 lakh bribe buried in lawn

description: India has lodged a strong protest with Canada concerning the anti-India parade in Toronto, which featured threatening language and unacceptable imagery targeting Indian leaders. The protest was registered with the Canadian High Commission in New Delhi, urging Canadian authorities to take action against elements promoting hatred and extremism.
title: India protests 'threatening imagery' at Canada parade: Report

description: The Archeological Survey of India (ASI) submitted a survey report to the Allahabad High Court regarding the Jama Masjid and Harihar temple dispute in Sambhal. The court has adjourned the case for the next hearing on May 13, extending the stay on trial court proceedings. The dispute centers on claims that the mosque was built after demolishing a temple.
title: Sambhal: ASI files survey report, HC fixes May 13 for next hearing

description: Persistent rain led to the abandonment of the match between Sunrisers Hyderabad and Delhi Capitals. DC, after a top-order collapse, recovered to post 133/7, thanks to Stubbs and Sharma's partnership. Cummins' impressive bowling spell put DC under early pressure. SRH are now out of the playoff race, while DC moved to fifth place.
title: SRH vs DC: Sunrisers officially knocked out of IPL 2025 playoff race

description: Following the deadly terror attack in Pahalgam, UN secretary-general Antonio Guterres on Monday addressed the escalating tensions between India and Pakistan, condemning the attack and offering UN assistance to restore peace. He emphasised that a military solution is not viable and expressed concern over the strained relationship, urging de-escalation and diplomacy.
title: UN chief condemns Pahalgam attack, offers help to ease India-Pak tensions

description: In anticipation of planned protests, Punjab Police conducted a crackdown, placing farm leaders under house arrest and detaining others. This action, endorsed by Chief Minister Bhagwant Mann, aims to prevent disruptions to public life caused by road and railway blockades. The move has sparked criticism and a call for further protests, escalating tensions between the government and farm organizations.
title: Ahead of Shambhu stir, farm leaders put under house arrest

description: Chechen leader Ramzan Kadyrov accused Elon Musk of remotely disabling a Cybertruck he claimed Musk gifted him, which Kadyrov had equipped with a machine gun for use in the SVO. Musk denied gifting the vehicle, raising questions about how Kadyrov obtained it, given US sanctions.
title: 'Musk behaved badly. He gives ...,' says Putin's close ally Ramzan Kadyrov

description: Rohit Sharma presented Mohammed Siraj with his T20 World Cup winning ring, as Siraj had missed the official ceremony during the BCCI's Naman Awards. Sharma acknowledged Siraj's vital role in India's victorious T20 campaign. The customized ring features the player's name, jersey number, and an Ashok Chakra, commemorating India's first major title since the 2013 Champions Trophy.
title: Rohit Sharma presents T20 World Cup winning ring to Mohammad Siraj

description: Congress leader Rahul Gandhi stated that India is capable of negotiating a fair trade deal with the US, acknowledging President Trump's right to adjust tariff structures. Speaking at Brown University, Gandhi stressed India's need to develop a robust manufacturing sector to rival China, emphasizing the importance of a liberalized economy for social progress.
title: Trump within his rights to negotiate tariffs, India capable of working out deal: Rahul Gandhi

description: Delhi Capitals struggled to 134 against Sunrisers Hyderabad after a disastrous start, recovering from 29/5 thanks to Ashutosh Sharma and Tristan Stubbs. Pat Cummins' fiery spell dismantled Delhi's top order, taking three wickets in the powerplay. Rain arrived immediately after the first innings, jeopardizing SRH's playoff chances and potentially impacting Delhi Capitals' IPL 2025 aspirations.
title: SRH faces playoff elimination if match ends in no result

description: Virat Kohli, a cricket legend, dreamt of emulating Sachin Tendulkar, revealed his childhood teacher Vibha Sachdev. Kohli balanced rigorous cricket practice with academics, often preparing for exams late due to training. Despite the challenges, teachers supported his dedication.
title: 'I will be the next Tendulkar': Virat Kohli’s teacher recalls his school days

description: India and the US are in trade talks, with India proposing zero-for-zero tariff arrangements on specific items like steel and pharmaceuticals, contingent on reciprocity and import volumes.
title: India offers zero-for-zero tariffs on auto parts, steel from US: Report

description: Stephen Curry's stellar performance propelled the Golden State Warriors to victory in Game 7 against the Houston Rockets. Curry scored 22 points, including 14 in the fourth quarter. Buddy Hield also contributed significantly with 33 points. The Warriors secured a 103-89 win. They now advance to face the Minnesota Timberwolves in the Western Conference Semi-Finals.
title: Stephen Curry shares message for teammates after Warriors beat Rockets

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack and escalating India-Pakistan tensions, major airlines like Lufthansa and Air France are rerouting flights to avoid Pakistani airspace. This comes after India closed its airspace to Pakistani carriers. Pakistan faces lost overflight revenue as airlines opt for alternative routes via Delhi, despite increased fuel costs and flight time.
title: India-Pak tensions hit skies as global airlines avoid Pakistani airspace

description: Jim Anderson, Coherent's CEO, topped US CEO pay in 2024 with $101.5 million, primarily from stock awards, surpassing prominent figures like Laxman Narasimhan and Satya Nadella. Median CEO compensation increased by 9.5% to $25.6 million, driven by a significant rise in stock-based compensation, now constituting 75% of total pay. Sundar Pichai's earnings decreased significantly to $10.72 million.
title: Meet highest-paid CEO in America, who earns more than CEOs of Google, Microsoft

description: Sultana Begum, claiming to be Bahadur Shah Zafar's great-granddaughter-in-law, faced disappointment as the Supreme Court dismissed her plea for the Red Fort's possession. The court deemed her petition "completely misconceived," shattering her hopes. Begum, who sought her ancestral home, expressed distress, questioning her future.
title: 'Did not want ...': Mughal emperor's 'heir' after SC rejects plea for Red Fort ownership

description: During the IPL 2025 match between Sunrisers Hyderabad and Delhi Capitals, Vipraj Nigam's run-out triggered a visible reaction from SRH owner Kavya Maran, quickly going viral. The dismissal occurred due to a miscommunication with Tristan Stubbs, ending Nigam's innings at 18 runs. Maran's expressive response was highlighted by Star Sports, emphasizing the excitement of the IPL playoffs race.
title: Watch: Kavya Maran's priceless reaction during SRH vs DC match

description: Elon Musk has refuted allegations linking him to extremist ideologies, dismissing them as a relentless propaganda campaign. In an interview, he defended his friendship with President Trump, stating they agree on most issues. Musk also accused the media of character assassination, suggesting they would harm him if they could, due to his association with the Trump administration.
title: A hurt Elon Musk tells Lara Trump: It is an outrageous thing to ...
US offers $1,000 to illegal aliens to leave country

description: Chinese President Xi Jinping will visit Russia soon. This visit occurs amidst reports of Chinese nationals fighting in Ukraine, mostly for Russia. Some fighters are returning with harrowing experiences. Ukraine accuses China of supplying Russia with war materials. China denies any state involvement. The situation poses a challenge for Xi, balancing support for Russia with avoiding direct military engagement.
title: What Xi's Moscow visit won't show: The Chinese dying for Russia

description: Following the Pahalgam attack, India has taken several actions against Pakistan. India suspended the Indus Waters Treaty and closed the Wagah-Attari border. Diplomatic ties were downgraded, and Pakistani diplomats were declared persona non grata. Visas for Pakistani nationals were revoked, and airspace was closed. Trade and shipping ties have been suspended.
title: Bleeding with thousand cuts: Steps India has taken against Pak since Pahalgam

description: Delhi Capitals have included T Natarajan, their expensive acquisition, in the playing XI for the first time, replacing Mukesh Kumar to strengthen their death bowling. Sunrisers Hyderabad won the toss and chose to field first at the Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium. Both captains emphasized the importance of executing their plans and maintaining a positive team environment as the league progresses.
title: Delhi Capitals unleash 10.75 crore player for the first time this IPL
From Australia to Canada: How Trump is making Left right again

description: Mumbai Indians head coach Mahela Jayawardene revealed that Rohit Sharma has been nursing a niggle since the Champions Trophy, explaining his usage as an impact substitute. Despite this, Sharma has scored 293 runs in 10 innings. MI, currently third with a strong Net Run Rate, needs two wins from their remaining three matches to secure a playoff spot.
title: MI head coach Mahela Jayawardene opens up on Rohit Sharma's injury

description: Indian cricketer Mohammed Shami has received a death threat via email, prompting an FIR to be filed in Uttar Pradesh's Amroha district. The sender, identified as Rajput Sindar, allegedly demanded a ransom of Rs one crore. Shami is currently playing in the IPL 2025 for Sunrisers Hyderabad.
title: Mohammed Shami faces death threat; FIR registered

description: The Central Board of Direct Taxes has released the updated ITR-2 form. It is for the assessment year 2025-26. The form includes separate reporting for capital gains. This is before and after July 23, 2024. Capital loss is allowed on share buybacks from October 1, 2024. The asset and liability reporting threshold is now Rupees one crore.
title: New ITR-2 form notified: Top changes for taxpayers
'Training students, evacuation plans': What May 7 mock drills will include
India demands Asian Development Bank cut funding for Pakistan

description: According to the IMF's World Economic Outlook April 2025, India is projected to become the fourth largest economy globally in 2025, surpassing Japan with a nominal GDP of $4,187.017 billion. The report indicates continued growth, forecasting India to overtake Germany by 2028 and achieve a $5 trillion economy by 2027.
title: India to become 4th largest economy in 2025, overtaking Japan

description: South African fast bowler Kagiso Rabada is cleared to play again after completing a substance abuse treatment program. This followed a positive test for a recreational drug during the SA20 competition in January. SAIDS confirmed Rabada tested positive after a match on January 21 and was informed on April 1, leading to a provisional suspension.
title: IPL 2025: Kagiso Rabada cleared to play, available for GT vs MI clash

description: Berkshire Hathaway's board has officially named Greg Abel as the next CEO, succeeding Warren Buffett by the end of 2026. Abel, currently vice-chairman overseeing non-insurance operations, will navigate the $900 billion conglomerate through global economic challenges. Buffett, 94, will remain chairman to ensure continuity, expressing confidence in Abel's leadership to maintain Berkshire's success.
title: Berkshire Hathaway board approves Greg Abel as CEO, backed by Warren Buffett

description: The Border Security Force is set to bolster its operational capabilities with 16 new battalions, adding approximately 17,000 personnel. This expansion follows initial approval and includes establishing forward headquarters for western and eastern commands, overseeing the Pakistan and Bangladesh borders. The move addresses heightened security concerns, particularly after political shifts in Bangladesh and recent terror attacks.
title: BSF plans to deploy 17K troops, set up HQs at Pak & B'desh borders

description: Chennai Super Kings face a setback. Wicketkeeper Vansh Bedi is out of IPL 2025. Urvil Patel replaces him. Patel is a wicketkeeper-batter from Gujarat. He had strong domestic performances. CSK is already out of playoff contention. The team will focus on future rebuilding. Patel's addition offers a glimpse into the next generation. CSK will play final games with pride.
title: CSK wicket-keeper ruled out of IPL 2025

description: President Vladimir Putin conveyed his condolences to Prime Minister Narendra Modi regarding the Pahalgam terror attack, assuring Russia's support in combating terrorism and emphasizing the need for justice. Both leaders affirmed their commitment to strengthening the India-Russia partnership.
title: Pahalgam attackers must be brought to justice, Putin tells PM Modi

description: The Allahabad High Court has dismissed a petition questioning Congress MP Rahul Gandhi's Indian citizenship. A BJP worker from Karnataka, S Vignesh Shishir, filed the petition. He alleged Gandhi possessed dual citizenship, making him ineligible to contest elections. The court had previously granted the Home Ministry time to verify information from the UK.
title: Allahabad high court dismisses plea challenging Rahul Gandhi's citizenship

description: India reigns supreme in ODI and T20I formats, securing the No. 1 spot in the latest ICC rankings, fueled by their Champions Trophy victory. New Zealand trails in ODIs, while Australia dominates the Test arena, despite a minor dip. England's Test resurgence propelled them to second, pushing India to fourth. The T20I rankings now encompass 100 teams, reflecting global participation.
title: ICC Rankings: India dominate white-ball formats, Australia top in Tests

description: Israel has formulated a new plan for Gaza, reportedly involving the territory's conquest and potential relocation of its population southward for safety. The Israeli security cabinet, led by Prime Minister Netanyahu, has approved the plan, aiming to defeat Hamas and secure the release of hostages. While Israel considers humanitarian aid distribution, concerns persist regarding the blockade's impact on Gaza's 2.
title: Israel 'unanimously approves' plan which includes Gaza 'conquest': Official
Joke row: SC summons Samay Raina, 4 others for 'mocking' the disabled

description: West Bengal Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee visited riot-affected Murshidabad, accusing the BJP-led Centre of instigating communal tensions. She alleged the BSF's actions escalated the violence and accused the BJP of forcibly relocating victims to prevent them from meeting her. Banerjee also criticized the NHRC's swift response to Murshidabad, questioning their absence in Manipur and Uttar Pradesh, suggesting a pre-planned conspiracy.
title: 'Murshidabad violence was well planned,' claims Mamata; blames BSF & BJP

description: Mixed Martial Arts will debut at the 2026 Asian Games. India's athletes need government and sponsor support. Currently, there are no awards or government funding for training. India lacks a recognized federation to govern MMA. Ritu Phogat and Puja Tomar highlight the financial struggles. They emphasize the need for training centers and coaches.
title: 'No help from government': MMA in Asian Games 2026 sparks concern

description: Amidst heightened tensions following the Pahalgam terror attack, Pakistan conducted a test flight of its home-made Fatah missile, capable of striking targets up to 120 kilometers. This launch, part of Exercise INDUS, aimed to validate the weapon's design and performance.
title: Pahalgam attack: Pakistan test-fires 2nd missile as tensions rise

description: Moody's Ratings warns that ongoing tensions with India pose a greater economic risk to Pakistan than to India. Pakistan's growth and fiscal consolidation could be hampered, straining foreign-exchange reserves. India's economy remains robust, with minimal impact expected.
title: Pak has more to lose than India: Moody's big warning

description: Amid escalating India-Pakistan tensions, India is enhancing storage capacity at two Kashmir hydroelectric facilities, marking its first action outside the Indus Waters Treaty after suspending it. Maintenance operations, including reservoir flushing to remove sediment, were conducted at the Salal and Baglihar projects.
title: Post IWT suspension, India begins expanding reservoir capacity in J&K

description: The Supreme Court has scheduled a hearing on May 15, before a bench led by CJI-designate B R Gavai, to address petitions challenging the constitutionality of the Waqf Amendment Act, 2025. This decision follows the Centre's pause on key aspects of the law and assurances given to the court regarding waqf property denotification and appointments to the Central Waqf Council.
title: SC lists PIL challenging Waqf case for hearing on May 15 by next CJI

description: Adani Group stocks surged following reports of discussions between Gautam Adani's representatives and US officials regarding bribery charges. The talks aim to dismiss criminal charges related to alleged bribery in Indian power supply contracts.
title: Adani stocks surge up to 14% after reports of team meeting Trump officials

description: The Supreme Court reprimanded a petitioner for filing a Public Interest Litigation (PIL) seeking tourist safety in hilly areas from terrorist attacks, deeming it a publicity stunt without genuine public concern. The court questioned the petitioner's motives and cautioned against demoralizing security forces with frivolous PILs, highlighting the judiciary's lack of expertise in terror investigation.
title: 'Aim to get publicity': SC rejects PIL seeking safety, security of tourists in J&K

description: Amazon's Andy Jassy and TCS's K Krithivasan are advocating for in-person work, emphasizing its importance for fostering company culture and driving innovation. Jassy believes that culture cannot be instilled remotely, while Krithivasan highlights the significance of mentorship and collaboration in a physical office setting.
title: Amazon CEO Jassy just said what TCS CEO told employees when it ended WFH

description: India A is set to tour England, with the first batch of players departing on May 25, as arranged by the BCCI. They will play three four-day games against England Lions, starting May 30, before the Test series. Senior players may participate in an unofficial Test for acclimatisation, depending on IPL progress and medical clearance.
title: India A likely to leave for England on May 25, BCCI begin process

description: Tim Paine has criticised the lack of transparency surrounding Kagiso Rabada's failed drug test, deeming the situation "extremely wrong." Paine argues that Rabada's positive test for a banned recreational substance during the SA20 league should not be concealed under "personal issues." He insists on public accountability, demanding clarity on the offence, punishment, and overseeing body.
title: 'It stinks': Ex-Aus captain slams lack of transparency in Rabada drug case

description: The Delhi Police arrested 24-year-old Vijay alias Lale in a hit-and-run and attempt-to-murder case involving a security guard at Mahipalpur Flyover. The accused allegedly ran over the victim after an argument over honking. The victim sustained serious leg injuries. A Mahindra Thar, identified via CCTV, was seized, and the arrest was made within six hours of the incident.
title: Told not to honk, Thar driver drives over security guard in Delhi

description: Singer Pawandeep Rajan, winner of Indian Idol Season 12, was critically injured in a car accident in Ahmedabad early Monday morning. The accident occurred around 3:40 a.m., leaving him with visible injuries. Fans are expressing their concern and sending wishes for his speedy recovery as they await official news regarding the cause of the accident and his current medical condition.
title: Indian Idol 12 winner Pawandeep Rajan injured in car accident

description: Uttar Pradesh Congress president Ajay Rai defended his "toy Rafale" jibe, clarifying it was to urge action against terrorism after the Pahalgam attack. Rai criticized the Defence Minister's symbolic gestures during the Rafale acquisition, demanding concrete action. BJP leaders strongly condemned Rai's remarks, accusing him of undermining military morale and aiding Pakistan, sparking a political controversy.
title: 'Just wanted to open eyes': Cong's Ajay Rai defends 'toy Rafale' jibe at Centre

description: Reliance Jio is strategically densifying its 5G network across India by deploying domestically manufactured network products, potentially slashing costs and reducing reliance on Ericsson and Nokia. This move involves utilizing 5G small cells produced near Chennai through a joint venture, enhancing coverage in urban areas. Jio's shift aims for self-reliance and optimized capital expenditure in its 5G expansion.
title: Reliance Jio’s in-house 5G push threatens European telecom giants

description: With his skill to swing the ball both ways and his dexterity to hit the 6m length consistently, Arshdeep Singh is arguably the best of his type India has had since Zaheer Khan. The 26-year-old's opening spell against Lucknow Super Giants (LSG) is a gentle reminder to Ajit Agarkar and co. of why he should be on the plane for the five-match Test series against England, starting June 20.
title: Arshdeep Singh: The left-arm quick India need in England

description: Elon Musk has once again altered his X display name, this time to 'Groklon Rust,' sparking speculation about its meaning. The moniker appears to blend references to Grok, Musk's AI chatbot, and the Rust programming language, potentially linked to xAI's infrastructure.
title: Elon Musk is no longer ‘Elon Musk’ on Twitter; changes his profile name to…

description: Aaron Finch suggests Rishabh Pant relinquish wicketkeeping to Nicholas Pooran to improve communication and leadership amid a poor IPL season. Pant's struggles with both batting and captaincy, highlighted by a slow scoring rate and on-field frustrations, are impacting LSG's performance. Finch believes this change could help Pant regain rhythm and directly manage the team's strategies, crucial for their playoff push.
title: 'Maybe it’s time he says, Pooran, you take ...': Finch's bold advice for Pant

description: Following the Pahalgam attack, India has banned all imports from Pakistan, including indirect routes via intermediary nations, postal services, and vessels. This action, triggered by national security concerns, aims to prevent Pakistani goods from entering India through circumvention.
title: Real blow to Pakistan! India chokes $500m goods via third countries

description: Police arrested eight individuals in connection with the murder of Suhas Shetty, revealing a revenge plot fueled by personal grudges. Abdul Safwan, targeted by Shetty's associates in 2023, allegedly orchestrated the murder with financial and logistical support from Adil Mehroof, whose brother was murdered in 2022, with Shetty named as an accused.
title: Revenge, rivalry, Rs 5L deal: Suhas Shetty murder linked to 2022 Fazil killing?

description: The Supreme Court dismissed Sultana Begum's plea to reclaim the Red Fort, deeming her claim as the widow of Bahadur Shah Zafar II’s great-grandson misconceived and meritless. The court questioned why only the Red Fort was being claimed and not other historical sites. Begum argued her family was wrongfully deprived of the fort after the 1857 war of independence.
title: SC rejects woman's plea claiming possession of Red Fort as legal 'heir'

description: Punjab Kings' head coach Ricky Ponting lauded Shreyas Iyer's captaincy, particularly the strategic promotion of Josh Inglis, which proved pivotal in their dominant victory against Lucknow Super Giants. Inglis' aggressive innings against Mayank Yadav shifted the momentum, while Prabhsimran Singh's explosive 91 and Arshdeep Singh's impactful bowling further solidified PBKS's win, propelling them to second place in the table.
title: 'Captain came up with the move': Ponting hails Shreyas' tactical call

description: Gold futures opened higher at Rs 93,271/10 grams, while silver saw a slight increase to Rs 94,145/kg. Prices previously declined due to optimism surrounding US-China trade talks and a stronger dollar.
title: Gold prices off record highs; Gold June futures start higher today
Indian student in US arrested for impersonating a 'federal agent' to dupe woman

description: Priyanka Gandhi Vadra stated that the central government's agreement to include caste enumeration in the upcoming census is due to pressure, highlighting Rahul Gandhi's advocacy on the issue. Jairam Ramesh criticized PM Modi for a "U-turn" on the caste census, noting the government's prior opposition.
title: 'My brother took up cause': Priyanka says govt 'pressured' for caste census

description: Prabhsimran Singh's explosive batting for Punjab Kings in the IPL is a source of joy for his ailing father, Surjit Singh, who is battling kidney failure. Despite his health struggles, Surjit finds solace and happiness in watching his son's performance. Prabhsimran has produced 437 runs in 11 innings for PBKS at a strike rate of 170.
title: Prabhsimran bats for ailing father, undergoing dialysis thrice a week

description: The Indian selection committee, led by Ajit Agarkar, is set to announce the squad for the England tour in May, with captaincy a key point of discussion. While Rohit Sharma's recent performance and Jasprit Bumrah's injury raise questions, the BCCI is considering Shubman Gill for a leadership role, potentially as vice-captain.
title: Shubman Gill being groomed for Test captaincy?

description: Warren Buffett, the legendary investor, acknowledged Tim Cook's role in Berkshire Hathaway's success. He credited Apple's CEO for significant financial gains. Buffett announced his retirement at the annual meeting. This marked the end of an era. Greg Abel, the vice chairman, is set to succeed Buffett. Abel will lead Berkshire with a focus on long-term value.
title: Warren Buffet: I am somewhat embarrassed to say Apple CEO Tim Cook ...

description: Virat Kohli, fondly known as 'Chiku,' owes his nickname to MS Dhoni's on-field mention and a childhood resemblance to a comic book character. Kohli clarified a recent social media interaction with Avneet Kaur's fan page, attributing it to an algorithmic error. This explanation followed a wave of speculation and memes online, highlighting the cricketer's constant presence in the news.
title: When Kohli revealed the secret behind his nickname ‘Chiku’

description: Gautam Adani's representatives have reportedly engaged with Donald Trump's administration officials to potentially dismiss criminal charges against him in a foreign bribery investigation.
title: Adani’s reps meet Trump officials; want end to US bribery cases

description: Security forces in Jammu and Kashmir's Poonch district discovered a large cache of arms and ammunition from a destroyed terrorist hideout, including IEDs and wireless sets. This discovery follows a recent deadly terror attack in Pahalgam, prompting heightened security measures across the state with increased checkpoints and deployments.
title: Army busts terror hideout in J&K's Poonch; IEDs, wireless sets, blankets recovered

description: Virender Sehwag advises struggling Rishabh Pant to rediscover his dominant form by reviewing past successes and maintaining his routine. Following a string of low scores and a concerning strike rate, Sehwag suggests Pant reconnect with his old self and seek guidance from MS Dhoni to clear doubts and regain confidence.
title: 'Call Dhoni, watch old videos': Sehwag's advice to out-of-form Rishabh Pant

description: BJP leaders have strongly criticized Congress, accusing them of demoralizing the Indian armed forces after Ajay Rai's "toy Rafale jet" comment was amplified by Pakistani media. The BJP alleges a conspiracy to undermine the army's morale, with Shehzad Poonawalla calling it a deliberate act of cooperation with Pakistan.
title: Congress leader's 'toy Rafale' jibe amplified by Pak media, draws BJP's ire

description: Gold price prediction: Last week, gold prices experienced their worst weekly decline in over two months, retreating from record highs due to easing trade tensions and mixed U.S. economic signals. Renewed trade talks between the U.S. and China, coupled with Trump's tariff relief measures, shifted investor interest towards the dollar and bonds.
title: Gold price prediction: What's the gold rate outlook for this week?

description: Seventeen-year-old Ayush Mhatre's impressive 94 off 48 balls against Royal Challengers Bengaluru highlights Chennai Super Kings' shift towards youth. Despite the loss, Mhatre's maturity and aggressive batting have drawn high praise from coach Stephen Fleming. His seamless integration into the CSK camp and ability to perform under pressure suggest a promising future with the franchise.
title: IPL 2025: Ayush Mhatre shows form, finesse beyond his years

description: Laughter Chefs season 2 takes an emotional turn with the contestants' mothers joining them on stage. Elvish seeks guidance from his mom, while Reem gets playfully roasted. Krushna shares a heartfelt story about his mother's best friend, Geeta, who raised him and Arti after his mother's passing, leading to tears from everyone.
title: Laughter Chefs: Krushna Abhishek breaks praising aunt Geeta for keeping her promise

description: Recent tensions escalate as Pakistan Army initiates unprovoked firing across the LoC, and with Pakistan demanding UNSC consultations. The Supreme Court is set to decide on the Waqf Amendment Act. Meanwhile, US President Trump imposes a 100% tariff on foreign films, citing threats to Hollywood. In sports, Rishabh Pant attributes LSG's defeat to misjudging conditions and costly errors.
title: Morning news wrap: Pakistan violates ceasefire again, SC to hear Waqf plea; and more

description: Stock market today: Nifty50 and BSE Sensex, the Indian equity benchmark indices, opened in green on Monday. While Nifty50 crossed the 24,400 mark, BSE Sensex was above 80,700.
title: Stock market today: Nifty50 above 24,400; BSE Sensex up over 250 points

description: Pakistani cricket legends, including Javed Miandad and Basit Ali, have expressed disappointment over Sunil Gavaskar's comments regarding Pakistan's Asia Cup participation. Gavaskar suggested political tensions might prevent Pakistan's inclusion, a statement Miandad found hard to believe, given their past camaraderie.
title: 'Stupid': Former Pakistani cricketers hit out at Gavaskar for Asia Cup remarks

description: Donald Trump has proposed the rebuilding and reopening of Alcatraz prison to house the country's most dangerous criminals, citing the need for a stricter approach to violent offenders. He has directed several federal agencies to collaborate on this project, envisioning an enlarged and rebuilt facility.
title: Trump plans to reopen Alcatraz: 10 things to know about the infamous prison

description: A recent study reveals that individuals in the early stages of Alzheimer's disease may exhibit difficulties with turning while walking. Researchers utilized virtual reality to identify navigational mishaps, potentially leading to simple diagnostic tests. The study found that those with early Alzheimer's overestimated turn angles and showed inconsistent directional orientation, distinguishing them from healthy older adults.
title: How early Alzheimer's may first show in walking and navigation

description: Lucknow Super Giants suffered a setback against Punjab Kings. The team lost by 37 runs. Rishabh Pant cited dropped catches as a key factor. Punjab Kings posted a formidable 236/5. Lucknow Super Giants only managed 199/7 in response. Ayush Badoni and Abdul Samad fought hard. Lucknow Super Giants now need to win their remaining matches.
title: 'Hurt us badly': Pant reveals major reason behind LSG's defeat vs PBKS

description: Bihar Chief Minister Nitish Kumar, acknowledging the Bharatiya Janata Party's role in his initial rise to power under then-Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee, has pledged his unwavering commitment to the BJP-led National Democratic Alliance. The Bihar CM attributed his past departures to party colleagues, specifically pointing to Lallan Singh's influence.
title: ‘My party made me go here and there’: Nitish Kumar on staying with NDA

description: Ajay Devgn's Raid 2 has stormed the box office, garnering an estimated Rs 70.75 crore during its opening weekend, fueled by strong advance bookings and positive reviews. The action-drama, directed by Rajkumar Gupta, features Devgn reprising his role as an IRS officer battling corruption, with Riteish Deshmukh as the antagonist.
title: Raid 2 box office collection day 4: Ajay Devgn starrer crosses Rs 70 cr mark

description: A Pakistani politician, Sher Afzal Khan Marwat from Imran Khan's PTI, stated he would flee to England if war with India broke out. This statement comes amid heightened tensions following a terrorist attack in Jammu and Kashmir.
title: Amid India-Pak tensions, Pakistan MP says he’ll head to England if war begins

description: Stock market recommendations: Motilal Oswal recommends Varun Beverages and JSW Infrastructure as top stock picks for the week starting May 5, 2025. VBL's strong Q1 performance, driven by volume growth and expansion, positions it well in India's beverage market. JSW Infrastructure's robust cargo volumes and strategic acquisitions are expected to fuel growth, capitalizing on India's infrastructure development.
title: Buy or sell: Stock recommendations for the week

description: Delhi Capitals, seeking to reignite their playoff aspirations, are set to clash with a struggling Sunrisers Hyderabad in a crucial IPL 2025 encounter. Axar Patel's fitness remains a concern as DC aims to overcome a two-match losing streak at home. SRH, despite boasting big names, are desperate to find form, making this match a high-stakes affair at Arun Jaitley Stadium.
title: IPL match today, SRH vs DC: All you need to know

description: Taylor Swift has been subpoenaed amidst a legal battle between Blake Lively and Justin Baldoni, stemming from accusations of sexual harassment and a subsequent $400 million countersuit. Swift's close friendship with Lively has drawn her into the case, potentially requiring her testimony. The situation unfolds as rumors swirl around Swift's relationship with Travis Kelce, further intensifying media attention.
title: Lawsuit storm hits Kelce as Taylor Swift dragged into Hollywood feud

description: A tragic case in Belgium highlights the dangers of improperly stored rice, where a young adult died from Bacillus cereus poisoning after consuming leftover spaghetti left at room temperature for days. This incident, known as 'fried rice syndrome,' underscores the importance of refrigerating cooked rice and pasta within two hours to prevent bacterial growth and potential health risks.
title: Leftovers can kill: Food poisoning bacteria you have never heard of

description: Wayne Gretzky, a Canadian icon, faces backlash for his friendship with Donald Trump, especially after Trump's remarks about giving Gretzky a 'pass.' This occurs amidst heightened political tensions between Canada and the U.S., fueled by Trump's past statements and trade disputes. Gretzky's actions, like wearing a MAGA hat and skipping Canadian colors, have sparked criticism and shifted Canadian sentiment.
title: 'Pretend you don’t know me': Gretzky faces backlash in Canada over Trump friendship

description: Pakistan has requested an emergency meeting with the UN Security Council to address escalating tensions with India, citing concerns over alleged aggressive actions and the suspension of the Indus Waters Treaty. The UNSC, under Greece's presidency, scheduled closed consultations for May 5 to discuss the matter.
title: UNSC to discuss rising India-Pakistan tensions after Pahalgam terror attack

description: Amid import surge concerns, recent data indicates a drop in electronics exports from China to both India and the US in January and February. Despite Trump's tariffs, no significant surge in shipments from China and ASEAN has been observed.
title: Eyes on electronics imports from China

description: Ajit Pawar's decades-long pursuit of Maharashtra's Chief Minister post remains elusive, marked by missed opportunities and political calculations. Despite his ambition and numerous stints as Deputy CM, the coveted position has been consistently out of reach. Meanwhile, Deven Bharti's appointment as Mumbai's police commissioner presents the challenge of re-establishing the force's presence and leadership in the city.
title: Ajit Pawar ‘still waiting to be CM’, says no ‘yog’ till now

description: The Municipal Corporation of Delhi (MCD) has completed only 21.3% of its drain desilting work by April 25, falling short of its May 31 deadline. Out of 1.3 lakh metric tonnes of silt targeted for removal, only 27,000 MT has been cleared from major drains. Residents report no desilting in their areas, leading to concerns about potential waterlogging during the monsoon season, further exposed by recent downpours.
title: Deadline looming, MCD met just 21% of desilting target by end of April

description: India's agricultural research body, ICAR, has developed two genome-edited rice varieties, 'DRR Dhan 100 (Kamala)' and 'Pusa DST Rice 1', promising a 20-30% yield increase. Agriculture Minister Shivraj Singh Chouhan anticipates a second green revolution with these climate-resilient, high-yielding crops. Expected to be available to farmers in two years, these varieties aim to save water, reduce methane emissions, and boost paddy production by 4.5 million tons across five million hectares.
title: ICAR: World’s first genome-edited rice varieties to boost yields 30%

description: Over 14 lakh candidates await the release of the subject-wise schedule for CUET-UG 2025, which is scheduled from May 8 to June 1. The NTA is yet to announce the exam dates and centre details, causing anxiety among aspirants. City intimation slips and admit cards are expected to be released soon on the official website.
title: NTA does it again, leaves 14L CUET-UG candidates without schedule, in limbo

description: In Delhi's Dabri area, an e-rickshaw driver, Rajendra, was arrested after he slashed a cab driver, Gagandeep Singh, in a road rage incident. Singh was attacked with a blade after a minor collision and is currently recovering. Police are investigating Rajendra's background for prior violent behavior. This incident follows another deadly road rage case in Ranhola where a motorcyclist was murdered after a dispute with an SUV driver.
title: Road rage: E-rickshaw driver slashes cabbie's neck

description: Donald Trump's recent announcement of a 100% tariff on foreign-made films has sparked concerns about a potential trade war. Citing the decline of Hollywood and alleged propaganda, Trump aims to revitalize American movie production. However, this move adds to existing trade tensions, particularly with China, impacting global supply chains.
title: Trump threatens 100% tariff on foreign-made movies
